              "text": "On 20 October 1986, after the demise of the late Sultan Omar Ali Saifuddien III, the cabinet was reshuffled which saw the introduction of new ministerial posts, namely the Ministers of Health and Religious Affairs, and Special Adviser in the Prime Minister's Office.",
              "links": [
                {
                  "type": "internal",
                  "page": "Sultan Omar Ali Saifuddien III"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "text": "The reshuffle saw the cabinet being enlarged to a total of 13 ministerial and 8 deputy ministerial posts."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "sentences": [
            {
              "text": "The cabinet was reshuffled again in 1988, 2005, 2010, 2015, 2018, and 2022."
            },
            {
              "text": "Since 2005, cabinet reshuffle typically happened every five years."
            },
            {
              "text": "However, the 2015 cabinet term lasted less than five years with a \"surprise\" reshuffle in 2018, with no official reason given, although it was speculated that corruption could be a reason."
            },
            {
              "text": "In contrast to the previous cabinets which served or intended to serve for five years, the 2022 cabinet shall serve for a four-year term."
            }
